entry.def: A build-up is a gradual increase in something.

example.ex: There has been a build-up of troops on both sides of the border...
example.tran: 边境两边都在集结兵力。

example.ex: The disease can also cause a build up of pressure in the inner ear leading to severe earache.
example.tran: 该疾病还会引起内耳的压力增加，从而导致剧烈的耳痛。

entry.def: The build-up to an event is the way that journalists, advertisers, or other people talk about it a lot in the period of time immediately before it, and try to make it seem important and exciting.

example.ex: We should wait at least until winter before we start the build-up to Christmas...
example.tran: 我们至少要等到冬天再开始着力营造圣诞节的气氛。

example.ex: The exams came, almost an anticlimax after the build-up that the students had given them.
example.tran: 在学生们一番忙碌准备之后，随之而来的考试却出乎意料地平淡。
